<TITLE> BCL leader injured in clash over land in Ctg </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Sep 11 (bdnews24.com)--The president of Bangladesh Chhatra League's Chittagong district (north) unit, Rajibul Hasan Suman, has been critically injured in a clash over occupation of a land. The incident took place at Biswa Colony under Khulsi Police Station of the port city early on Friday. Awami League district (North) unit general secretary M A Salam told bdnews24.com some local hoodlums hacked Suman when he had gone to take possession of his purchased land. But the locals said Suman sustained injury in mob beating as he went to grab graveyard land. Salam said, "The seriously injured Suman was admitted to Chittagong Medical College Hospital around 7am." 'Khokon', the owner of the land, was also injured during the clash, he said A resident at the colony refusing to named told bdnews24.com some 30-40 youths led by Suman came to capture the graveyard land adjacent to the mosque just after Fazr prayer early on Friday. The locals caught and beat them, he said. Though Suman is under treatment at Chittagong Medical College Hospital, his name was not registered in the patient lists, bdnews24.com chittagong office said. When contacted, Khulsi police chief Iftekhar Hasan told bdnews24.com on Friday evening that he knew nothing about it. b
